Here's the updated plan with a dedicated UI/Design stage:

School Master Account System - Final Plan
Stage 1: Foundation (Database & Basic Structure)
Create schools table
Create school_invitations table
Create school_audit_log table
Modify users table: add school_id and role
Stage 2: School Admin Registration & Dashboard
School admin signup flow
School Dashboard page (license usage, school details, logo upload)
API routes for school registration and retrieval
Stage 3: Invitation System
Invite Educator page with email input
Bulk invite option (paste email list)
Email sent via Resend with unique invite link
Pending invitations list with status
Stage 4: Educator Accept & Onboarding
Invite landing page (shows school name, validates code)
Signup form (email prefilled, no payment required)
Account linked to school, audit log entry created
Stage 5: Educator Management
Educator Management page listing all educators
Remove educator (frees license)
Password reset for educators (by school admin)
Educator self-removal option
Stage 6: Subscription & Access Control
License count enforced (can't invite if at limit)
7-day grace period on subscription expiry
Read-only mode during grace (can export work)
Warning notifications before expiry
Stage 7: Invite Reminders & Polish
Auto-resend pending invites after 7 days
Expiry notifications
Invite cancellation by admin
Stage 8: UI Refinement & Visual Harmony
Apply warm earth-tone palette (#D7C3AA, #C4A882) consistently across all school pages
Ensure generous whitespace and breathing room
Subtle card layouts with soft shadows
Gentle transitions and hover states
Typography aligned with existing Montessori theme
Mobile responsiveness
Consistent button styles (sandy secondary buttons)
Visual polish pass on all school-related interfaces
Stage 9: Admin Tools (Your Backend)
Set license count for schools
Activate/suspend schools
View all schools and their educators




Stripe Setup for Schools
You'll need to create a per-seat price in Stripe:

Product: "Guide School Subscription"
Price: Per-seat pricing (e.g., $10/seat/month or $100/seat/year)
Billing: Use Stripe's "quantity" feature - when a school buys 15 seats, you charge quantity: 15
The minimum 10 seats is enforced in your code, not in Stripe.

Self-Service School Signup Plan
Here's the flow:

Landing Page (auxpery.com.au) → User enters:

School name
Admin email
Number of seats (dropdown: 10, 15, 20, 25, 50, 100+)
API Call → Creates Stripe Checkout with quantity: seats

After Payment → Webhook creates:

School record with invite code
Admin user account
Redirects admin to Guide to set password
Admin Dashboard → School admin can:

Copy invite link
See license usage
Add more seats later